The paper deals with a generalization of the stable marriage problem, which is a well-studied problem in computer science and falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also presents algorithms and complexity results, which are typical topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The use of linear programming and graph theory suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of combinatorial optimization (cs.GT) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
